cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.IT 

This paper deals with advanced resource reservation in ultra high-speed networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AL (Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory) due to the use of multi-commodity flow arguments. The paper also discusses the use of simulations and benchmarks, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
